</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Drive gear feed media shaft 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Shaft-transmission-assy-stage-2 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-1156E15C-FA11-42F7-80CE-F9823F371FA9" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Function</title><p class="- topic/p "> This test will use the media initialization procedure to determine the roll radius of the media. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The roll radius is very important as it is the key input to determine how many media is fed. This has a direct effect of the functioning of the buffer. A lot of components are used in the execution of this test. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The outcome of the test should be stable. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Use the service media for this test. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-E414ED4B-6985-4372-8BA5-D0F5A519E38B" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Procedure</title><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Start the test. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Optional: Load the service media in the drawer 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Select the roll you want to test. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Execute the measurement. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Verify the outcome on the selected roll. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Execute the test a few times to confirm that the outcome is stable. 
</p></li></ol></section><section id="GUID-153080C1-7F86-4B67-A78B-A11CB36CE413" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Values</title><p class="- topic/p "> Three values are shown: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The radius 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The diameter 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The circumference 
</p></li></ol><p class="- topic/p "> The manually measured radius must not differ more than 5 mm from the test result. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In case the value of the radius is too high or too low: See 
<xref keyref="12diag_analyze_12_6_103" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-BD00AB80-F81D-4189-8CC6-A9F441B49A7E.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="tsTroubleshooting"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>12 Analyze if the value of the radius in SDS 12-6-103 is not OK</xref> 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-27CCE224-3251-485B-9B12-9B573BC82940.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>SDS</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
